189
00:18:52,302 --> 00:18:54,904
但无法以GPS定位就没辙
but the GPS-jamming negates that.

190
00:18:55,038 --> 00:18:58,975
地对空飞弹的存在只能用…
And a surface-to-air threat necessitates
a low-level laser-guided strike

191
00:18:59,075 --> 00:19:00,343
F-18以低空雷射引导攻击
tailor-made for the F-18.

192
00:19:00,477 --> 00:19:01,478
我认为…
I figure

193
00:19:02,045 --> 00:19:04,047
最少要投掷两枚精准炸弹
two precision bombs minimum.

194
00:19:04,180 --> 00:19:06,716
两架一组，出动四架战机
Makes it four aircraft flying in pairs.

195
00:19:07,183 --> 00:19:09,352
飞离峡谷必须垂直爬升
That is one hell of a steep climb out of there

196
00:19:09,486 --> 00:19:11,888
暴露在地对空飞弹攻击范围内
exposing you to all the surface-to-air missiles.

197
00:19:12,555 --> 00:19:13,857
就算成功爬升
You survive that

198
00:19:14,924 --> 00:19:16,693
回程也得一路和敌机交战
it's a dogfight all the way home.

199
00:19:16,826 --> 00:19:19,362
你拥有这一切的实战经验
All requirements for which you have real-world experience.

200
00:19:20,063 --> 00:19:22,132
并不全在同一项任务中
Not in the same mission sir.

201
00:19:25,101 --> 00:19:26,102
不
No.

202
00:19:28,905 --> 00:19:31,207
有人会无法活着回来
No someone's not coming back from this.

203
00:19:31,341 --> 00:19:32,909
到底可不可行？
Can it be done or not?

204
00:19:33,510 --> 00:19:35,245
工厂几时会开始运作？
How soon before the plant becomes operational?

205
00:19:35,378 --> 00:19:37,113
三周后，也许更早
Three weeks. Maybe less.

206
00:19:38,615 --> 00:19:41,117
我很久没开F-18战机，而且…
Well it's been a while since I've flown an F-18 and...

207
00:19:42,118 --> 00:19:44,721
我不确定能信任另外三名飞行员
I'm not sure who I'd trust to fly the other three.

208
00:19:44,854 --> 00:19:46,956
但我会想出办法
But I'll find a way to make it work.

209
00:19:47,090 --> 00:19:48,692
你误会了，上校
I think you misunderstand Captain.

210
00:19:49,259 --> 00:19:50,060
长官？
Sir?

211
00:19:50,160 --> 00:19:53,530
我们不要你飞，而是要你当教官
We don't want you to fly it. We want you to teach it.

212
00:19:56,399 --> 00:19:57,767
教官？
Teach sir?

213
00:19:59,169 --> 00:20:02,806
我们召回十二名扞卫小组毕业学员
We've recalled 12 TOPGUN graduates from their squadrons.

214
00:20:02,939 --> 00:20:05,575
你要从中细选出六名飞行员
We want you to narrow that pool down to six.

215
00:20:06,142 --> 00:20:07,911
让他们执行任务
They'll fly the mission.

216
00:20:09,546 --> 00:20:11,081
上校，有问题吗？
Is there a problem Captain?

217
00:20:12,949 --> 00:20:15,085
你明知道有…长官
You know there is sir.

218
00:20:16,319 --> 00:20:17,120
是啊
Yeah.

219
00:20:17,954 --> 00:20:20,323
布莱德利布雷德萧，也就是公鸡
Bradley Bradshaw aka "Rooster."

220
00:20:20,457 --> 00:20:22,192
你和他老爸曾是搭档
I understand you used to fly with his old man.

221
00:20:22,325 --> 00:20:24,094
他的呼号是什么？
What was his call sign?

222
00:20:25,061 --> 00:20:26,563
“呆头鹅”，长官
"Goose" sir.

223
00:20:26,663 --> 00:20:27,831
他的死是很不幸
Tragic what happened.

224
00:20:27,964 --> 00:20:29,833
米契尔上校被裁定没犯错
Captain Mitchell was cleared of any wrongdoing.

225
00:20:29,966 --> 00:20:31,935
呆头鹅的死是意外
Goose's death was an accident.

226
00:20:32,068 --> 00:20:33,570
你是这么想吗？
Is that how you see it Captain?

227
00:20:33,670 --> 00:20:35,805
呆头鹅的儿子也是这么想吗？
Is that how Goose's son sees it?

228
00:20:38,842 --> 00:20:41,811
恕我直言，长官，我不是教官
With all due respect sir I'm not a teacher.

229
00:20:41,945 --> 00:20:43,480
你当过扞卫小组教官
You were a TOPGUN instructor before.

230
00:20:43,613 --> 00:20:45,849
那是三十年前，只撑了两个月
That was almost 30 years ago. I lasted two months.

231
00:20:45,982 --> 00:20:47,283
我不属于那里
It's not where I belong.

232
00:20:47,417 --> 00:20:49,619
我就老实跟你说吧
Then let me be perfectly blunt.

233
00:20:49,753 --> 00:20:53,089
你不是我的首选，其实根本不在名单上
You were not my first choice.
In fact you weren't even on the list.

234
00:20:53,790 --> 00:20:56,226
举荐你的人是卡赞斯基上将
You are here at the request of Admiral Kazansky.

235
00:20:57,127 --> 00:21:00,697
我非常景仰冰人
Now Iceman happens to be a man I deeply admire

236
00:21:00,830 --> 00:21:03,833
他认为你对海军仍能有所贡献
and he seems to think that
you have something left to offer the navy.

237
00:21:04,834 --> 00:21:06,703
我想不出是什么
What that is I can't imagine.

238
00:21:08,038 --> 00:21:09,873
你不必接下这工作
You don't have to take this job.

239
00:21:10,006 --> 00:21:11,307
但恕我直言
But let me be clear:

240
00:21:11,441 --> 00:21:14,244
这会是你最后一项任务
This will be your last post Captain.

241
00:21:15,979 --> 00:21:19,549
当学校的教官，不然就退出海军
You fly for TOPGUN or you don't fly for the navy ever again.

242
00:21:27,991 --> 00:21:30,026
我赌20块你不能正中红心三次
Twenty bucks you can't get three in a row.

243
00:21:42,472 --> 00:21:44,674
（冰人：“怎么搞得这么僵？”）

244
00:21:47,877 --> 00:21:53,683
（那个孩子还没能准备好执行这项任务）

245
00:21:53,817 --> 00:21:55,885
（冰人：“没有人能

246
00:21:56,019 --> 00:21:57,921
所以才会把你找来”）

247
00:22:00,990 --> 00:22:04,828
（你可以先警告我）

248
00:22:04,928 --> 00:22:08,098
（冰人：“讲了你还会来吗？”）

249
00:22:11,301 --> 00:22:13,570
真不敢相信
Oh you've got to be kidding me.

250
00:22:16,072 --> 00:22:17,173
彼得
Pete.

251
00:22:18,675 --> 00:22:19,776
潘妮？
Penny?

252
00:22:20,744 --> 00:22:24,047
-你在这里干嘛？
-我才要问你呢
-What are you doing here?
-I should ask you the same thing.

253
00:22:25,315 --> 00:22:27,617
-说来话长
-我不信
-Well that is a long story.
-I doubt that.

254
00:22:27,630 --> 00:22:28,470
Yeah.

255
00:22:28,618 --> 00:22:30,320
你这次又惹毛了谁？
Who'd you piss off this time?

256
00:22:30,453 --> 00:22:31,955
另一位少将
Another admiral.

257
00:22:32,088 --> 00:22:33,089
那就对了
Exactly.

258
00:22:35,892 --> 00:22:37,894
-你还在生我气吗？
-彼得
-Are you mad at me?
-Oh Pete.

259
00:22:38,862 --> 00:22:42,065
我没办法一直生你气，那就是问题
I can never stay mad at you. That's the problem.

260
00:22:43,400 --> 00:22:44,734
我得说…
I got to say

261
00:22:44,868 --> 00:22:48,304
我以为永远不会在北岛航空站碰到你
North Island is the one place
I thought for sure I'd never run into you.

262
00:22:48,938 --> 00:22:51,875
-你来了多久？
-三年前顶下这地方
-How long you been here?
-Bought this place about three years ago.

263
00:22:51,975 --> 00:22:53,777
-三年前？
-是啊
-Three years?
-Yeah.

264
00:22:53,910 --> 00:22:58,281
就在你惹毛另一位少将被派去沙漠之后
Not long after you got shipped off to the desert
for pissing off that other admiral.

265
00:22:59,149 --> 00:23:01,317
那是三年前的事？
That was three years ago?

266
00:23:02,485 --> 00:23:04,721
你一定惹上大麻烦
You must be in a lot of trouble.

267
00:23:05,221 --> 00:23:07,290
否则不会自愿回来这里
No way you'd come back here willingly.

268
00:23:09,092 --> 00:23:10,093
不过呢…
Well

269
00:23:11,127 --> 00:23:12,629
你会想办法解决
you'll sort it out.

270
00:23:13,229 --> 00:23:14,464
不，我想…
No I think...

271
00:23:15,932 --> 00:23:18,268
-这是最后一次
-少来了
-I think this is it.
-Come on Pete.

272
00:23:18,368 --> 00:23:21,071
我认识你以后你就一直这么说
You've been saying that as long as I've known you.

273
00:23:21,171 --> 00:23:24,974
你开F-18载我兜风被逮到也这么说
You said it after they busted you
for taking me on a joyride in that F-18.

274
00:23:25,442 --> 00:23:27,977
没过多久你就被派去波士尼亚
Then the next thing I know you're off to Bosnia.

275
00:23:28,511 --> 00:23:30,980
然后去伊拉克，两次都有去
Then Iraq. Both times.

276
00:23:31,114 --> 00:23:32,916
你每次惹上麻烦…
You get yourself in trouble

277
00:23:34,017 --> 00:23:36,853
只要冰人打通电话你又能飞
Iceman makes a call and you're back in the air.

278
00:23:36,986 --> 00:23:38,388
潘妮，这次不同
Penny this is different.

279
00:23:38,521 --> 00:23:39,923
彼得，相信我
Pete trust me

280
00:23:40,023 --> 00:23:42,325
也许现在看似不可能
as improbable as it seems right now

281
00:23:42,459 --> 00:23:45,862
但你一定会再坐上战机出任务
somehow you'll be back in a fighter plane
with your tail on fire.

282
00:23:47,097 --> 00:23:48,798
-潘妮…
-太迟了
-Penny...
-Too late.

283
00:23:48,932 --> 00:23:49,966
什么？
What?

284
00:23:50,100 --> 00:23:52,035
你本来要问我几点下班
You were about to ask me what time I get off.

285
00:23:55,772 --> 00:23:57,374
别用那副表情看我
Don't give me that look.

286
00:23:58,608 --> 00:24:01,111
我没用什么表情看你，我发誓
I'm not giving you any look. I swear.

287
00:24:01,778 --> 00:24:04,147
我们每次的结局都一样，彼得
It always ends the same with us Pete.

288
00:24:05,782 --> 00:24:07,550
这次就别再来一次
Let's not start this time.

289
00:24:12,055 --> 00:24:12,889
好吧
Okay.

290
00:24:13,790 --> 00:24:14,791
很好
Okay.

291
00:24:19,562 --> 00:24:20,997
你看起来挺好的
You look good.

292
00:24:31,007 --> 00:24:32,709
多谢了，老兄
Much appreciated pal.

293
00:24:35,412 --> 00:24:36,513
发生什么事？
What am I missing?

294
00:24:37,981 --> 00:24:38,915
（冒犯女士、海军，或把手机放吧台 就得请一轮酒）

295
00:24:39,049 --> 00:24:42,886
“冒犯女士、海军，或把手机放吧台
"Disrespect a lady the navy or
put your cell phone on my bar..."

296
00:24:43,019 --> 00:24:44,854
就得请一轮酒”
"...and you buy a round."

297
00:24:45,355 --> 00:24:46,456
请每一个人？
For everyone?

298
00:24:46,589 --> 00:24:49,325
这就是规矩，幸好时候还早
I'm afraid rules are rules. You're lucky it's early.

299
00:24:50,560 --> 00:24:52,095
拜托！
Oh come on!

300
00:24:52,829 --> 00:24:54,764
看看谁来了？
What do we have here?

301
00:24:56,399 --> 00:24:58,702
原来是凤凰
If it ain't Phoenix!

302
00:24:58,835 --> 00:25:01,104
我还以为我们全是菁英，郊狼
And here I thought we were special Coyote.

303
00:25:02,672 --> 00:25:05,475
没想到连逊咖都被找来
Turns out the invite went to anyone.

304
00:25:06,242 --> 00:25:08,011
大伙儿，这是捕手
Fellas this here's Bagman.

305
00:25:08,111 --> 00:25:09,779
-刽子手
-随便你
-Hangman.
-Whatever.

306
00:25:10,246 --> 00:25:12,549
他可是唯一一名海军飞行员
You're looking at the only naval aviator on active duty

307
00:25:12,682 --> 00:25:14,017
曾在空战击落敌机
with a confirmed air-to-air kill.

308
00:25:14,117 --> 00:25:14,918
别说了
Stop.

309
00:25:15,051 --> 00:25:19,055
不过对方开的是韩战时期的古董战机
Mind you the other guy was in a museum piece
from the Korean War.

310
00:25:19,189 --> 00:25:21,858
-冷战
-不同的战争，同一个世纪
-Cold War.
-Different wars same century.

311
00:25:21,958 --> 00:25:22,892
不是这个世纪
Not this one.

312
00:25:23,026 --> 00:25:24,461
你朋友是谁？
Who are your friends?

313
00:25:24,594 --> 00:25:26,563
-复仇者
-粉弟
-Payback.
-Fanboy.

314
00:25:26,696 --> 00:25:28,698
-嘿，郊狼
-嘿
-Hey Coyote.
-Hey.

315
00:25:28,798 --> 00:25:30,233
-他是谁？
-谁是谁？
-Who's he?
-Who's who?

316
00:25:33,370 --> 00:25:34,738
你几时进来的？
When did you get in?

317
00:25:35,271 --> 00:25:37,374
我一直都在这里
I've been here the whole time.

318
00:25:37,941 --> 00:25:39,976
-他开匿踪战机
-他能隐形
-The man's a stealth pilot.
-Literally.

319
00:25:40,110 --> 00:25:42,579
我是武器系统操作官
Weapons systems officer actually.

320
00:25:43,146 --> 00:25:44,714
毫无幽默感
With no sense of humor.

321
00:25:46,649 --> 00:25:47,884
他们叫你什么？
What do they call you?

322
00:25:48,485 --> 00:25:49,886
巴布
Bob.

323
00:25:49,986 --> 00:25:51,087
你的呼号啦
No your call sign.

324
00:25:53,990 --> 00:25:54,991
巴布
Bob.

325
00:25:55,625 --> 00:25:56,493
巴布佛洛伊德
Bob Floyd.

326
00:25:57,327 --> 00:26:00,163
你就是我新的武器官？
You're my new backseater? From Lemoore?

327
00:26:01,398 --> 00:26:02,999
看来是这样，对啊
Looks like it. Yeah.

328
00:26:06,669 --> 00:26:08,104
打一场撞球
Nine-ball Bob.

329
00:26:08,805 --> 00:26:09,606
把球排好
Rack 'em.

330
00:26:11,608 --> 00:26:12,942
好吧
Okay.

331
00:26:13,510 --> 00:26:15,478
-亲爱的潘妮
-是
-Penny my dear.
-Yeah.

332
00:26:15,612 --> 00:26:17,814
再来四杯啤酒，老头子请客
I'll have four more on the old-timer.

333
00:26:34,664 --> 00:26:36,032
布雷德萧
Bradshaw!

334
00:26:36,966 --> 00:26:38,334
是你吗？
Is that you?

335
00:26:44,140 --> 00:26:46,009
原来你回美国啦？
This is how I find out you're stateside?

336
00:26:46,142 --> 00:26:47,977
对啊，我想给你个惊喜
Yeah I just thought I'd surprise you.

337
00:26:50,980 --> 00:26:53,116
我也给你个惊喜
I guess I surprised you back.

338
00:26:54,784 --> 00:26:56,519
-见到你真好
-我也是
-It's good to see you.
-Good to see you too.

339
00:26:59,155 --> 00:27:00,824
-来吧
-谢谢
-Here you go.
-Thank you.

340
00:27:00,957 --> 00:27:02,826
谢啦，老爹
Much appreciated Pops.

341
00:27:10,166 --> 00:27:12,969
趁人少的时候帮我结帐吧
How about ringing me up before the evening rush?

342
00:27:27,183 --> 00:27:28,418
布雷德萧
Bradshaw.

343
00:27:28,551 --> 00:27:30,020
没想到你会来
As I live and breathe.

344
00:27:31,054 --> 00:27:31,821
刽子手
Hangman.

345
00:27:31,921 --> 00:27:34,157
你看起来…还不赖
You look... good.

346
00:27:35,358 --> 00:27:37,027
我是很厉害，公鸡
Well I am good Rooster.

347
00:27:39,062 --> 00:27:40,063
我超厉害的
I'm very good.

348
00:27:40,563 --> 00:27:41,998
老实说
In fact

349
00:27:42,098 --> 00:27:43,833
我厉害到没人信
I am too good to be true.

350
00:27:43,933 --> 00:27:45,235
所以…
So

351
00:27:45,368 --> 00:27:47,771
有人知道为什么把我们找回来吗？
anybody know what this special detachment is all about?

352
00:27:47,904 --> 00:27:50,940
任务就是任务，我不问为什么
No mission's a mission. They don't confront me.

353
00:27:51,908 --> 00:27:54,878
我只想知道，谁会是队长？
What I want to know: Who's gonna be team leader?

354
00:27:55,512 --> 00:27:59,516
又有哪几个够资格跟我出任务？
And which one of y'all has what it takes to follow me?

355
00:28:01,117 --> 00:28:04,521
刽子手，跟你只会提早进棺材
Hangman the only place you'll lead anyone is an early grave.

356
00:28:13,296 --> 00:28:16,966
跟你只会…耗尽燃油
Well anyone who follows you is just gonna run out of fuel.

357
00:28:18,034 --> 00:28:20,136
你就像只公鸡，对吧？
But that's just you ain't it Rooster?

358
00:28:21,104 --> 00:28:23,473
只会窝在驾驶舱
You're snug on that perch

359
00:28:23,606 --> 00:28:25,909
等着永远都不会来的…
waiting for just the right moment...

360
00:28:28,044 --> 00:28:29,212
大好机会
that never comes.

361
00:28:32,749 --> 00:28:34,651
我超爱这首歌
I love this song!

362
00:28:41,825 --> 00:28:43,426
他一点都没变
Well he hasn't changed.

363
00:28:44,461 --> 00:28:46,663
是啊，还是老样子
Nope. Sure hasn't.

364
00:28:51,134 --> 00:28:52,168
你们看
Check it out.

365
00:28:53,269 --> 00:28:54,437
又来了一群
More patches.

366
00:28:55,105 --> 00:28:57,974
哈佛、耶鲁、奥马哈，靠，那是费兹
That's Harvard Yale Omaha. Shit that's Fritz.

367
00:28:58,108 --> 00:29:00,343
这是什么任务？
What the hell kind of mission is this?

368
00:29:01,344 --> 00:29:03,346
我们不该问这问题
That's not the question we should be asking.

369
00:29:04,114 --> 00:29:06,116
大家都是顶尖高手
Everyone here is the best there is.

370
00:29:07,717 --> 00:29:09,686
谁能当我们的教官？
Who the hell are they gonna get to teach us?

371
00:29:12,956 --> 00:29:14,657
信用卡刷不过
It's been declined.

372
00:29:15,125 --> 00:29:15,925
你在开玩笑
You're kidding.

373
00:29:31,808 --> 00:29:34,044
大伙儿，来吧
